(
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995D6588B6438AFA4A" box="[873,997,1491,1510]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="4.[833,860,653,667]" captionStartId-1="4.[833,860,1226,1240]" captionStartId-2="5.[85,112,1115,1129]" captionTargetBox-0="[880,1456,150,622]" captionTargetBox-1="[880,1455,736,1191]" captionTargetBox-2="[133,708,150,1084]" captionTargetId-0="figure@4.[880,1456,150,623]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[880,1456,735,1195]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[132,708,150,1084]" captionTargetPageId-0="4" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="Fig. 4. Holotype female of Augochlorella mavricera sp. nov. (A) Habitus; (B) frontal view of head; (C) dorsal view of mesosoma. Scale bar: 0.5mm." captionText-1="Fig. 5. Paratype male of Augochlorella mavricera sp. nov.(A) Dorsal view; (B) frontal view of head; (C) ventral view of genitalia.Scalebar:A and B at0.5 mm,Cat 0.25mm." captionText-2="Fig. 6. Ventral view of male metasoma and hind leg. (A) Metasoma of A. acarinata; (B) hind leg of A. acarinata; (C) metasoma of A. mavricera sp. nov.; (D) hind leg of A. mavricera sp. nov. S4 apical margin indicated in red. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677420" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677422" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677424" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677420/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677422/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3677424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Figs. 4–6C,D</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31CF0E9FFDEFF995D4D888A440BF8B5" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB9A362FFDEFF995D4D888A440BF8B5" blockId="4.[833,1504,1462,1985]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995D4D888A43C7F9AE" bold="true" box="[833,936,1519,1538]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The female of this species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995B87888B4302F9B2" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995B87888B4302F9B2" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The body of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995DF78B6F4417F9B2" authority="Gonçalves, 2019" authorityName="Gonçalves" authorityYear="2019" box="[1019,1144,1546,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mavricera" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995DF78B6F4417F9B2" box="[1019,1144,1546,1566]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. mavricera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241C20BFFDEFF995A738B6E44A1F9B2" box="[1151,1230,1547,1566]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is mostly dark green with some violet reflections on clypeus and supraclypeal area and black dorsal surfaces of terga (
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995A4D8B264416F9FA" box="[1089,1145,1603,1622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[833,860,653,667]" captionTargetBox="[880,1456,150,622]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[880,1456,150,623]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Holotype female of Augochlorella mavricera sp. nov. (A) Habitus; (B) frontal view of head; (C) dorsal view of mesosoma. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677420/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) while 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995AC58B24452FF9F9" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" box="[1225,1344,1601,1621]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995AC58B24452FF9F9" box="[1225,1344,1601,1621]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is bright green with some copper reflections. Also, 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995AB98B38455DF9DD" authority="Gonçalves, 2019" authorityName="Gonçalves" authorityYear="2019" box="[1205,1330,1629,1649]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mavricera" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995AB98B38455DF9DD" box="[1205,1330,1629,1649]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. mavricera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A241C20BFFDEFF995B358B3A45E6F9DE" box="[1337,1417,1631,1650]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
punctation is sparser than on 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995A2B8B1C44F3F921" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" box="[1063,1180,1657,1677]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995A2B8B1C44F3F921" box="[1063,1180,1657,1677]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(i&gt;2pd on lower paraocular and i&gt;pd on mesoscutum). The male can be easily separated of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995B988BF0431CF969" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995B988BF0431CF969" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dark body, including legs (
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995AD88BD7457AF969" box="[1236,1301,1714,1733]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[833,860,1226,1240]" captionTargetBox="[880,1455,736,1191]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[880,1456,735,1195]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 5. Paratype male of Augochlorella mavricera sp. nov.(A) Dorsal view; (B) frontal view of head; (C) ventral view of genitalia.Scalebar:A and B at0.5 mm,Cat 0.25mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677422/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995B448BD7450AF969" box="[1352,1381,1714,1733]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[85,112,1115,1129]" captionTargetBox="[133,708,150,1084]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[132,708,150,1084]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 6. Ventral view of male metasoma and hind leg. (A) Metasoma of A. acarinata; (B) hind leg of A. acarinata; (C) metasoma of A. mavricera sp. nov.; (D) hind leg of A. mavricera sp. nov. S4 apical margin indicated in red. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">6D</figureCitation>
), compared with yellowish color of 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995A358BA844DFF94D" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" box="[1081,1200,1741,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995A358BA844DFF94D" box="[1081,1200,1741,1761]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995ACC8BAB4573F94D" box="[1216,1308,1742,1761]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[85,112,1115,1129]" captionTargetBox="[133,708,150,1084]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[132,708,150,1084]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 6. Ventral view of male metasoma and hind leg. (A) Metasoma of A. acarinata; (B) hind leg of A. acarinata; (C) metasoma of A. mavricera sp. nov.; (D) hind leg of A. mavricera sp. nov. S4 apical margin indicated in red. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 6A,B</figureCitation>
). The S4 is slightly bilobed (
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995D978B8F43B0F951" box="[923,991,1770,1789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[85,112,1115,1129]" captionTargetBox="[133,708,150,1084]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[132,708,150,1084]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 6. Ventral view of male metasoma and hind leg. (A) Metasoma of A. acarinata; (B) hind leg of A. acarinata; (C) metasoma of A. mavricera sp. nov.; (D) hind leg of A. mavricera sp. nov. S4 apical margin indicated in red. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) in the new species, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C06D8E1FFDEFF995AFE8B8C4508F951" authorityName="Coelho" authorityYear="2004" box="[1266,1383,1769,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlorella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinata">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995AFE8B8C4508F951" box="[1266,1383,1769,1789]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">A. acarinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have S4 strongly bilobed (
<figureCitation id="133DBFE7FFDEFF995A1E8A634436F8B5" box="[1042,1113,1798,1817]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[85,112,1115,1129]" captionTargetBox="[133,708,150,1084]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[132,708,150,1084]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 6. Ventral view of male metasoma and hind leg. (A) Metasoma of A. acarinata; (B) hind leg of A. acarinata; (C) metasoma of A. mavricera sp. nov.; (D) hind leg of A. mavricera sp. nov. S4 apical margin indicated in red. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677424/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31CF0E9FFDEFF9B5D4D8A474115FB3B" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="4" pageNumber="95" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB9A362FFDEFF985D4D8A474461FB3B" blockId="4.[833,1504,1462,1985]" lastBlockId="5.[804,1475,152,1985]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="96" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995D4D8A4743D2F899" bold="true" box="[833,957,1826,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995DC18A4744ECF899" bold="true" box="[973,1155,1826,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">
<typeStatus id="54BD1DC0FFDEFF995DC18A474441F899" box="[973,1070,1826,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Holotype</typeStatus>
female
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995A988A44450AF899" box="[1172,1381,1825,1845]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Measurements (mm)</emphasis>
. Eye notch width: 1.3; head length: 1.6; glossa length: 0.6; clypeus width: 0.7; clypeus length: 0.4; supraclypeal length: 0.3; clypeus ocellar distance: 0.9; intertegular distance: 1.1; T1 width: 1.7; T2 width: 1.8; body length: 7.0. 
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDEFF995A3A8AF54407F808" box="[1078,1128,1936,1956]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="95">Head</emphasis>
. Labrum basal elevation orbicular, black. Mandible black with subapical amber spot; subapical tooth not strongly produced; longsetae (2–3 OD) on outer and ventral margins. Epistomal angle orthogonal. Clypeus sparsely punctate, weakly microreticulateon basalportion; erect setae with 1–1.5 OD; apical surface darkened, subapical area violet, remaining surface bright green. Supraclypeal area sparsely punctulate, polished; fine erect setae; green with violet reflections. Paraocular area punctate, strongly microreticulate; olive green, some weak violet reflections near eye notch; branched setae with 1–1.5 OD. Antennae; scape dark brown with very weak metallic highlights, flagellomeres weakly amber ventrally; F1–3 setose, with inconspicuous sensilla, remaining flagellomeres with conspicuous sensilla. Frons not depressed; conflected punctate, strongly microreticulate; olive green; short and fine setae. Preoccipital ridge not carinate. Vertex coarsely punctatebecoming rugose nearridge; longplumose (short branches) setae. Genapuncticulate, microlineateonpostgena; dark green to black; white plumose setae (1.5–2 OD). Hypostomal ridge carinate. 
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDFFF985EB98BF04173F905" box="[181,284,1685,1705]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Pronotum dorsal ridge weakly carinate; lateral angle not projected, rounded; lateral ridge rounded; dorsal surface lineate and puncticulate; dark green; with few tomentum on dorsal surface. Propleuron brown with green highlights. Prosternum green. Fore leg: coxa dark green, trochanter and femur brown, tibiabrownonoutersurface, baseof tibiaandpretarsuslight brown; long yellowish setae on coxa to femur, yellow erect setae ontibiaandtarsus. Mesoscutumanteriorborder weaklyacuminate; median sulcus well impressed; parapsidal lines weakly impressed; punctate laterally, more sparse on median surface (i=pd), microlineations more conspicuous on anterior surface; green with violet reflections; short (=OD) and sparse white setae. Scutellum median sulcus very weakly impressed; punctate to conflected punctate, microreticulate; bright olive green; longersetae (=2.5–3 OD) on posterior margin. Mesepisternum conflected punctate, microreticulate; olive green, weak violet reflections; covered with plumose setae (=1.5 OD). Mid leg brown; yellow setae on femur to tarsus. Tegula concentric lineate; dark amber, weak greenreflections anteriorly. Fore wing: marginal cell apex rounded; membrane hyaline; black microtrichia. Metanotum median sulcus very weakly impressed; rugulose, microreticulate; green with bluish iridescence; long plumose setae (2–3 OD). Metepisternum lineate above superior metapleural pit, conflected punctate below; green with violet reflections. Hind leg: basitibial plate apex rounded; tibial spur serrate; brown; long plumose setae on ventral coxa to femur, ventral tibial setae not too long and with short branches. Hind wing hyaline. Metapostnotum weakly inclined; weakly depressed; apex rounded to trapezoidal; less twice as long as metanotum; rugulose on median surface, carinate laterally, microreticulate; dark olive green with some violet reflections; Propodeum posterior surface puncticulate, few scattered punctures, microreticulate to granular; dark olive green; short plumose and some erect (1–2 OD) setae.Propodeum lateralsurface puncticulate, microreticulate; olive green; with thicker and longer (3–4 OD) setae. 
<emphasis id="B9727F70FFDFFF985B358F9845F0FCBD" box="[1337,1439,765,785]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="96">Metasoma</emphasis>
. T1 anterior and dorsal surfaces not angled between; sparsely puncticulate, microlineate; olive greenreflections on lateral surfaces, black on median surface, few copper reflections elsewhere; short. T2 puncticulate; olive greenreflections on lateral surfaces, black on median surface, few copper reflections elsewhere; short. T3–T4 puncticulate; olive green reflections on lateral and marginal surfaces, black on median surface, few copper reflections elsewhere; short.T5 punctate; darkbrown; coveredwith blacklongerect setae. Pygidial plate short, truncate. S1 without tubercle; lineate; amber with greenhighlightson mediansurface; verylongsetae (=3 OD) on mediansurface. S2–4 lineate; browntolight brown; subapical setae verylong (about 5 OD) and with recurved apices. S5 lineate; brown; longsetae (about 4 OD), plumose. S6 lineate; brown; yellowish setae on apical margin.
</paragraph>
